  "prompt": "Which type of energy produce by steam?",
  "response": "Steam is used to produce mechanical energy in a process commonly associated with steam engines or turbines. This mechanical energy can then be converted into electrical energy. The process involves water being heated to produce steam, which expands and applies pressure to move pistons or turn turbine blades, thus generating mechanical energy. In power plants, this mechanical energy is often converted into electrical energy using generators. Therefore, steam is crucial in producing both mechanical and electrical energy.",
